Date: Mon, 28 Dec 1998 15:42:42 -0600
From: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>
Source: MSNBC-28 Dec 1998, edited

MORA COUNTY, New MexicoÂ– The state is reporting a new case of anthrax in
Mora County, on the same ranch where the bacteria killed a cow this summer.
Blood tests confirmed a cow dumped in a Raton landfill was infected with
anthrax.
Ranchers vaccinated the rest of the herd, but one cow that came into the
herd did not get its shots and contracted anthrax. It died three days ago.
